@startuml TASFA_Unified_Server_Authoritative

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderThickness 2
skinparam BoxBorderThickness 2
skinparam MaxMessageSize 120
hide footbox

actor "Browser Client" as Client
participant "FileUploadQueue\none active file" as Queue
participant "Upload Worker\nHTTP/XHR" as Uploader
participant "Download Worker\nHTTP/XHR" as Downloader

box "TASFA Server" #F8F8F8
    participant "Upload API" as UploadAPI
    participant "Download API" as DownloadAPI
    participant "HTP Engine\nserver-authoritative" as HTP
    participant "Predictor\nRTT + guard signals" as Predictor
    participant "Worker Scheduler\nsticky round-robin" as Scheduler
    participant "Finalize Cache\nasync completion" as FinalizeCache
    database "Storage\nupload.bin.part\nmeta.*\nstate.*\nhtp.bin\nsession.lock" as Storage
end box

== Routes ==

note over Client,DownloadAPI
Upload:
POST /file/upload/init
POST /file/upload/status
POST /file/upload/renegotiate
POST /file/upload
POST /file/upload/complete
POST /file/upload/cancel

Download:
GET /file/download/:id/handshake
GET /file/download/:id/chunk/:chunk_index
GET /file/download/:id
GET /assets/tasfa/img/:filename/handshake
GET /assets/tasfa/img/:filename/chunk/:chunk_index
GET /assets/tasfa/uploads/:filename/handshake
GET /assets/tasfa/uploads/:filename/chunk/:chunk_index
end note

== File-Level Sequential Upload Queue ==

Client -> Queue: select one or more files
Queue -> Queue: create asset, preview card,\nand HTP session per file
Client -> Queue: Upload queued files
Queue -> Uploader: start first pending file
note right of Queue
Only one file uploads at a time.
The next file starts after the active
file succeeds or fails.
end note

== Upload Session Init ==

Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload/init\n(file metadata, link hints)
UploadAPI -> Storage: preallocate upload.bin.part\ncreate meta.*, state.*, htp.bin, session.lock
UploadAPI --> Uploader: upload_id, token, chunk_size,\ncurrent_parallel_chunks, max_parallel_chunks,\ndispatch_pacing_ms, modulus_M,\nupload_secret, stream_key_hex,\nstream_iv_seed_hex, group_count,\nclient_stripes
note right of Uploader
chunk_size is a session contract because it
defines chunk_index * chunk_size file offsets.
Learned chunk-size hints apply to the next
TASFA session.
end note

== Chunk Preparation and Upload ==

loop For each plaintext chunk
    Uploader -> Uploader: SHA-512(plaintext chunk)\nraw_scalar = first_8_bytes % M

    group Complete 6-slot HTP group
        Uploader -> Uploader: compute L1,L2,L3\nbalance only v3 and v5
    end

    note right of Uploader
    The last partial chunk is sent once with its
    exact byte range. No padding or splitting.

    Incomplete final 6-slot groups are excluded
    from HTP validation; they are never padded.
    end note

    Uploader -> Predictor: Wynn/Aitken guard from quality samples
    alt Very low predicted quality
        Uploader -> Uploader: send this chunk through\nparallel AES-256-GCM fallback
    else Normal or guarded path
        Uploader -> Uploader: use adaptive parallel window\n(trim one slot when guarded)
    end

    Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload\nchunk bytes
    note right
      Headers:
      X-TASFA-Upload-ID
      X-TASFA-Upload-Token
      X-TASFA-Chunk-Index
      X-TASFA-Hash-Tag
      X-TASFA-Raw-Scalar
      X-TASFA-Magic-Scalar
      optional X-TASFA-Stream-Mode: aes-256-gcm
      optional X-TASFA-Chunk-RTT
    end note

    UploadAPI -> Scheduler: submit by upload_id hash
    Scheduler -> UploadAPI: dispatch to same worker
    UploadAPI -> Storage: check dense bitmap state.bin
    alt New chunk or server retry target
        UploadAPI -> Storage: pwrite(chunk, chunk_index * chunk_size)\nwrite one bitmap byte in state.bin
        UploadAPI -> HTP: store hash_tag, raw_scalar,\nand magic_scalar in htp.bin
        UploadAPI -> Predictor: add RTT sample if supplied
        UploadAPI --> Uploader: 204 No Content\nX-TASFA-Accepted: 1\nX-TASFA-Chunk-Complete: 1
    else Duplicate chunk not in retry_targets
        UploadAPI --> Uploader: 204 (discarded)\nX-TASFA-Accepted: 1\nX-TASFA-Chunk-Complete: 1
    end
end

== Upload Adaptation ==

Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload/status\nor POST /file/upload/renegotiate
UploadAPI -> Predictor: Lagrange tail RTT extrapolation\n(max 8 samples, clipped to 30s)
Predictor --> UploadAPI: predicted_remaining_ms\nparallel window recommendation
UploadAPI --> Uploader: current_parallel_chunks,\nmax_parallel_chunks,\npredicted_remaining_ms
Uploader -> Uploader: increase window after clean completions\nreduce one slot after failures

== Runtime Baselines ==

note over Uploader,Downloader
Upload chunk size: 16 MiB desktop, 8 MiB mobile.
Upload chunk-size hint range: 8 MiB minimum,
up to 32 MiB desktop or 16 MiB mobile.

Download chunk size: 8 MiB desktop, 4 MiB mobile,
up to 32 MiB when the client hints a larger session.
Download coalesce (span group): up to 16 chunks on good links.

Default browser upload parallelism is 16.
Max upload parallelism capped at 40.
Max concurrent upload sessions capped at 64.
Upload and download maximum windows are server-defined
or backed by blog.settings.
Upload XHR timeout is adaptive and at least 180s.
Upload session fetch timeout is 30s.
end note

== Completion and Server-Authoritative HTP ==

Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload/complete
UploadAPI -> FinalizeCache: mark started (202)
FinalizeCache -> Scheduler: spawn finalize worker
Scheduler -> UploadAPI: run complete_sync
UploadAPI -> Storage: flock(session.lock); count received chunks from state.bin

alt Some chunks are still missing
    UploadAPI --> Uploader: not finalized; missing chunks remain
else All chunks received
    UploadAPI -> HTP: load per-chunk records from htp.bin
    HTP -> HTP: validate only complete\n6-slot groups

    alt Scalar order permuted in a group
        HTP -> HTP: brute-force 720 permutations\nreorder htp.bin records if invariant restored
    end

    alt All complete groups pass
        HTP --> UploadAPI: validation OK
        UploadAPI -> Storage: SHA-256 finalization\ncommit file and store delete PIN hash
        UploadAPI --> Uploader: 200 OK\nfile_id, url, checksum, delete_pin
        Uploader -> Queue: mark active file complete
        Queue -> Uploader: start next queued file

    else One or more groups fail
        HTP -> HTP: hybrid HTP-XOR recovery\nlocate suspect via topology scores\nreconstruct single missing chunk via parity P\nmulti-erasure falls back to ARQ
        HTP -> HTP: derive per-slot suspicion scores\nscore = in_fail / total_fail
        note right of HTP
        Slot line coverage:
        v0: L1,L3
        v1: L1
        v2: L1,L2
        v3: L2
        v4: L2,L3
        v5: L3

        Slots that only appear in passing equations
        are cleared from the suspect list.
        end note

        HTP -> HTP: evaluate repair_worthwhile\nat least 3 suspects and retry_cost exceeds repair_cost

        alt Direct retry is cheaper
            HTP --> UploadAPI: retry_targets = all suspects\ncontraction_level = 0
        else Repair is worthwhile
            HTP -> HTP: contract each level-0 group to\naggregate = (r12 * r23) % M
            HTP -> HTP: form higher-level 6-slot groups\nand re-evaluate line invariants

            alt Contraction narrows suspects
                HTP --> UploadAPI: narrowed retry_targets\ncontraction_level += 1
            else Contraction inconclusive
                HTP --> UploadAPI: original suspects\ncontraction_level += 1
            end
        end

        UploadAPI -> Storage: persist retry_targets,\nsuspicion_scores, contraction_level
        UploadAPI --> Uploader: 409 needs_retry\nretry_targets, suspicion_scores,\ncontraction_level, retry_reason
    end
end

FinalizeCache -> FinalizeCache: cache result for polling

== Retry Target Retransmission ==

loop For each server-issued retry target
    Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload\n(retransmit chunk)
    UploadAPI -> Storage: confirm chunk_index is in\nhtp_retry_targets
    UploadAPI -> Storage: overwrite chunk bytes\nand update bitmap
    UploadAPI -> HTP: replace hash_tag, raw_scalar,\nand magic_scalar
    UploadAPI -> Storage: remove chunk from retry_targets
    UploadAPI --> Uploader: 204 No Content\nX-TASFA-Accepted: 1\nX-TASFA-Chunk-Complete: 1
end

Uploader -> UploadAPI: POST /file/upload/complete
UploadAPI -> FinalizeCache: check cache
alt Cache hit (done)
    FinalizeCache --> UploadAPI: cached status + body
else Cache miss (still running)
    FinalizeCache --> UploadAPI: 202 processing
end

== Download Protocol ==

Client -> Downloader: request download
Downloader -> DownloadAPI: GET .../handshake\npreferred chunk-size hint
DownloadAPI --> Downloader: session_id, session_token,\nchunk_size, chunk_count,\nconcurrency hints,\nstream_key_hex, stream_iv_seed_hex

loop Adaptive chunk groups
    Downloader -> DownloadAPI: GET .../chunk/:chunk_index\n?span=N&chunk_rtt_ms=...
    DownloadAPI -> Storage: read contiguous chunk range
    DownloadAPI -> Predictor: add RTT sample\nestimate remaining time
    DownloadAPI --> Downloader: chunk bytes\nX-TASFA-Chunk-Index\nX-TASFA-Chunk-Count\nX-TASFA-Predicted-Remaining-Ms
    Downloader -> Downloader: requeue short reads,\ntimeouts, and network errors by chunk index
    Downloader -> Downloader: grow span and parallelism\nafter successful chunk groups
end

note right of Downloader
For progressive video/audio the client assembles
chunks sequentially inside a bounded forward window.
Failed chunks record a retry time and release the slot;
the scheduler never skips a byte range or closes
the stream early.
end note

Downloader -> Client: assemble one contiguous buffer

== Storage and Hardening ==

note over UploadAPI,Storage
Upload session files:
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/upload.bin.part
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/meta.json
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/meta.bin
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/state.json
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/state.bin
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/htp.bin
data/tasfa/uploads/{upload_id}/session.lock

There is no blocks.bin or chunk_counts.bin.
Chunk completion is one O(1) bitmap byte per chunk.

Upload IDs and tokens are random hex strings.
Session locks use flock on session.lock
to prevent racing bitmap writes.

Session metadata stores hash_tags, magic_scalars,
htp_retry_targets, htp_suspicion_scores,
and htp_contraction_level.
end note

@enduml
